Guard add_subdirectory(test) behind if(BUILD_TESTING).

test/Geometry/CMakeLists.txt calls set_property(TEST <names> ...) at top level,
but those tests are only registered by cet_test() when BUILD_TESTING is ON. With
-DBUILD_TESTING=OFF (the packaging default), cet_test() no-ops, so the tests do
not exist and set_property() hard-fails at configure time:

  CMake Error at test/Geometry/CMakeLists.txt:177 (set_property):
    set_property given TEST names that do not exist: geometry_test ...

Only descend into test/ when BUILD_TESTING is ON. Upstream-worthy: a tests-off
configure should not fail. See conda/potential_improvements.md.
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -43,6 +43,8 @@ add_subdirectory(larcorealg)
 add_subdirectory(larcorealg)

 # tests
-add_subdirectory(test)
+if(BUILD_TESTING)
+  add_subdirectory(test)
+endif()

 # ups - table and config files
